<subSubSection id="252DC6E5939CB96FFAB307CBA54C3DE2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D59625BFD2AB3E0BC9A23B12D8FF3E66" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="7EA47B54CA452811616B286BDE16466E" baseAuthorityName="Terayama" baseAuthorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Acrepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acrepyris tainanensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tainanensis">Acrepyris tainanensis</taxonomicName>
Terayama, 1995: 143, figs 11-14. Holotype (male, HUS), type loc.: Raisha, Taiwan; paratype (male, HUS), type loc.: Kanshirei; paratype (male, NIAES), type loc.: Kuanzuling, Tainan Hsien. 
<taxonomicName id="3AC4EA40FA913A6B0B0A5B8DD437F606" baseAuthorityName="Terayama" baseAuthorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristepyris tainanensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tainanensis">Pristepyris tainanensis</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="F14D2D2E12AC58948C12E63AABDB6C4B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4489.1.1" author="Azevedo, CO" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 294" refId="B8" refString="Azevedo, CO, Alencar, IDCC, Ramos, MS, Barbosa, DN, Colombo, WD, Vargas, RJM, Lim, J, 2018. Global guide of the flat wasps (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae). Zootaxa 4889 (1): 1 - 294, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4489.1.1" title="Global guide of the flat wasps (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4489.1.1" volume="4889" year="2018">Azevedo et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
: 104 (genus transfer).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D79FD9D8585EF13086A727C297FDB08A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="male diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E8172A5691D7DD16ED467C947EDC819F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8328C1473227AF3ACB094D025D74D16A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
TL ≈ 8.6 mm. HL/HW 
<normalizedToken id="A74264B53FD84CA1AAE0415B9685D4E9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
100 = 103. Frons and vertex with shallow foveolae (ca. 0.05-0.06 mm in diameter), of which intervals are smooth and shining and narrower than diameter of foveolae. Anterior clypeal margin nearly straight medially. Mandible with five apical teeth. Transverse pronotal carina present. Cervical pronotal area in lateral view forming an angulate corner. LP/WP = 0.96. Metapostnotal median carina not complete posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F39CB3415B079790B4C4D5F0CB0CD5A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="female diagnosis">
<paragraph id="852FF16F983410C6618336F69946B885" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96C69F5812B253A6365581B19747C5C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3E092FF2E93BD48BBCC4F7976FEBDF02" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="4F45BA7EFA615DB0CCA13BEBEE27F44D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="41ECD3DEB42A2F64EAE69F8E6E0C379D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Full description was given by 
<bibRefCitation id="770F5D546C41ED5800DED4D6E408C52C" author="Terayama, M" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="139 - 145" refId="B31" refString="Terayama, M, 1995. Taiwanese species of the genus Pristocera (Hymenoptera, Chrysidoidea, Berthylidae). Japanese Journal of Entomology 1: 139 - 145" title="Taiwanese species of the genus Pristocera (Hymenoptera, Chrysidoidea, Berthylidae)." volume="1" year="1995">Terayama (1995)</bibRefCitation>
. Additional information as below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DCA125DC5AEB069617E449AAAF6083E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="C577EF919264B3DA374E1E855FFA140A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="133B66DE335D9E4EDB693120B2F6BBF0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Frons and vertex with deep foveolae (ca. 0.05-0.06 mm in diameter), of which intervals are smooth and shining; intervals in vertex and frons usually narrower than diameter of foveolae. Occipital carina present. Median portion of clypeus roundly produced anteriad; median clypeal carina moderately distinct, almost reaching anterior margin; anterior clypeal margin truncate, nearly straight medially. Compound eye large and convex. Mandible with five teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7CD1DD4FAEB0BEF1BD95F9E64CAB6594" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="D0EA26591B870D2FCEE90B812200E948" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="91B1C866888E215957E2DC0016471499" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Dorsal area of pronotum smooth and shining, with deep foveolae; distinct transverse carina(e) present (arrow in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2BE4D0FBB5F4061729171F850E031675" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Pristepyris tainanensis, male, paratype A head in full-face view B mandible C mesosoma in lateral view (mirror-reversed); arrow indicating an angulate corner present on cervical pronotal area D mesosoma in dorsal view; arrow indicating transverse pronotal carinae present. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.84953.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686038" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">10D</figureCitation>
); cervical pronotal area in lateral view forming an angulate corner (arrow in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="58B9FEC7D5411202A9EB64769A443C03" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Pristepyris tainanensis, male, paratype A head in full-face view B mandible C mesosoma in lateral view (mirror-reversed); arrow indicating an angulate corner present on cervical pronotal area D mesosoma in dorsal view; arrow indicating transverse pronotal carinae present. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.84953.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686038" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">10C</figureCitation>
). Mesopleuron elongate; anterior, upper and lower fovea distinct; acropleural area smooth and shining. Mesopleural pit absent. Lateral face of metapectal-propodeal complex irregularly rugose. Metapectal-propodeal complex in dorsal view with LP/WP = 0.96, with lateral margins subparallel and slightly convex; metapostnotal median carina distinct, but incomplete posteriorly; submedian rugae irregularly running and incomplete posteriorly; sublateral margin incomplete posteriorly; posterior transverse margin weak; dorsomedian and dorsolateral faces weakly rugoso-scabrous; median portion of propodeal declivity transversely rugoso-scabrous.
</paragraph>
<caption id="87FD7ED9AFF872E018BDDE55EE2F5EBF" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.84953.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686038" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 10" startId="F10">
<paragraph id="EF5DA0EBC34FC8F95BADD18D6B8633BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="D79358884E2B4BE3F0839EEECE31125F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2CF370B09E00ED282303C100AB60D72A" baseAuthorityName="Terayama" baseAuthorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristepyris tainanensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tainanensis">
<emphasis id="98FA12E27694F0620265C41BA25C0E7F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pristepyris tainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male, paratype 
<emphasis id="AF0768A361F798B669FEE1BE2ED7CEAC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
head in full-face view 
<emphasis id="E219FCDAE75AC245AD4B055AB7DE83A3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
mandible 
<emphasis id="F5F366E638B218E92B5A820251A9EDDF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C</emphasis>
mesosoma in lateral view (mirror-reversed); arrow indicating an angulate corner present on cervical pronotal area 
<emphasis id="7AE3D8BCF4199372292D629D0FEF399D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D</emphasis>
mesosoma in dorsal view; arrow indicating transverse pronotal carinae present. Scale bars: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5A4DDA1AA9AC5BEE06798DEF22E48D6E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="12AE7A1814AD71F034127700365B2B49" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="26673E2ED2569EEE22FCF24D12116DCA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="93812165B8129BA4EC27BB90AF7E2EEF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="taxonomic remarks">
<paragraph id="F7EEDA999A3063CAD1C220355CE1E78A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Taxonomic remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3AFDCD11AB625B9E04A6F2CA1064A132" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="BB110C614B435838318F9E027A80B766" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristepyris ishigakiensis." order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ishigakiensis.">
<emphasis id="31F37AD39C781904495963FDC193A66F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pristepyris ishigakiensis.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
The two species share two remarkable features: mandible is five-toothed; cervical pronotal area in lateral view forming an angulate corner (arrow in Figs 
<figureCitation id="BBB43DD2A80DF307220C97F9E35F55C5" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pristepyris ishigakiensis, male, A-E, G, H, JI 170808 _ 34, F, TH 190717 _ 42 A head in full-face view B antenna (right) C mandible D mesosoma in lateral view; arrow indicating an angulate corner present on cervical pronotal area E mesosoma in dorsal view; arrows indicating posterior transverse margin extending to spiracle F mesosoma in dorsal view; arrow indicating transverse pronotal carina present G forewing H hindwing. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.84953.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686034" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="74C3520A38ED47065E2B57DDDEF0EB1A" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Pristepyris tainanensis, male, paratype A head in full-face view B mandible C mesosoma in lateral view (mirror-reversed); arrow indicating an angulate corner present on cervical pronotal area D mesosoma in dorsal view; arrow indicating transverse pronotal carinae present. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.84953.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686038" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">10C</figureCitation>
). However, no metasomal and genital morphology is given in the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="2EE3AC3F5D4AA3A43DE976DD1C569128" genus="P." lsidName="P. tainanesis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tainanesis">
<emphasis id="B4AD3056119D2A8B5C3CEAE37AA0771A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. tainanesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the present authors had no opportunity to dissect and examine the male genitalia of the type material. Therefore, it is impossible to conclude whether the two morphospecies are conspecific or not and 
<taxonomicName id="C7ED358714A746F3C1751140AADB0A0C" genus="P." lsidName="P. tainanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tainanensis">
<emphasis id="F61DF837FC553190F628DD154A511132" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. tainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is tentatively treated as an independent species. The identity will be discussed when the 
<normalizedToken id="081F8E180CE403E2854F7886E5F858C6" originalValue="“topotypes”">&quot;topotypes&quot;</normalizedToken>
of 
<taxonomicName id="308EBA95F5C896B65CBE601DC376BBA3" genus="P." lsidName="P. tainanesis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tainanesis">
<emphasis id="5103D7C5C115F97D8A0A1E9126AA3832" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. tainanesis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
become available in the future.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="31ECB87FB3E964BF39CDF287E9B72CC5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="70CAD783AFAB31FBA5EFAB21393317FD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD2FD6AFAED67885A63C36885BDF6C85" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Southern Taiwan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
